\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Impartial Third stepped up to the edge of a barren plateau. Far below her painted toes lay a red rock valley. This valley coursed into a desert, where its dry riverbed choked on sand. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 How could she remain impartial at such a sight? That valley and its river once sustained an idyllic clime. She recalled the memory wildflowers, endless fields of them. She longed for their sweet aroma to stick to her hair again, and oh, how she used to delight in the excitement every little butterfly and bee. Chirping birds hunted those drunken swarms, and the meat of those birds fed foxes, and all of them, at different stages of life, from womb to carrion corpse, fed lizards. The meat of the lizards fed larger birds, and on the circle went. She presided over it all, measuring out fates alongside the Creative First and the Destructive Second. Their balance weaved a tapestry which was beautiful in all its joy and sorrow. Now, that circle of life was fossilized under a thick layer of compacted sand, and the only things growing on the surface were lichens.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They looked like brown rags, those lichens. They sustained nothing but themselves as they soaked up the evening mist. Then there was the blood from all the dead soldiers. Those favored sons and daughters were not native to this soil, but another layer of sand would soon erase any proud distinctions.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She stepped off the cliff.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her white robes clung to her body as she fell. The wind ripped tears from her eyes. Better for her that she should die instead of be stuck in this confused and ugly world. Better for her, but only her; for everyone else, she needed to see her purpose through. Only, she would no longer remain impartial. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She clenched her fists and swerved out of her fall with the power of flight. She zipped through the red rock valley. She followed its course out into the desert, tracing the sinuous route of the dead river through the battlefield. On any other day, the sweep of carnage below her would have made her sick. On this day, those fields of silent dead brought her a somber peace, for if she had her way, this would be the last battle ever waged. And what a horrible battle it was, still raging\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the rim of the world was red with a line of fire that had been burning for days. The sky above it was black with a rolling cloud of smoke. That dark cloud\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s immensity was so great that it could be called a god in its own right, deserving of a name. Its stomach flashed with }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 lightning, and whatever peace she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d felt was subsumed by the distant drum of sequent thunder.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She bit her lip to keep from weeping.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Embarrassed, she wiped her cheek clean from the stain of tears. Now, she bit her lip in anger, because all those people below her were dead, and and elsewhere more were dying, and she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d thought to pity herself.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her selfishness was appalling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Unconscionable.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Remembering her purpose, she sped towards the setting sun. Far beyond the sprawl of embattled dead, she saw her destination: a lonely red rock circle trimmed with standing stones. The Creative First and Destructive Second were already there, positioned as far apart as the circle allowed, which for them, was not far enough.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Impartial Third picked up speed, then swept down to alight upon the stone with a whirlwind. The Creative First scowled at this dramatic entrance. The Destructive Second did not stir at all. She sat}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  on a drop cloth stool with her back turned to the circle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s center. Her shaved head was aimed at the red line of war which churned the world over. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her white robes were slipping off her shoulders, and fashioned as they were from transparent silk they left nothing to the imagination, even where the material bunched. It was not seductive, and neither was it meant to be. The Destructive\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s dark philosophy was strange and heavy on symbols; she wore transparent clothing to draw attention to the artifice of false boundaries, how they disguised naked and uncomfortable truths.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The First and Second detested each other. As a word, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91rival\u8217\'92 was not strong enough to capture their enmity. And a bitter enmity it was. Their conflict was near enough to the root of all troubles.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thank you for coming,\u8221\'94 the Impartial Third said to them both.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Creative\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s scowl deepened. \u8220\'93You well know that we are bound to your call.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Impartial ___. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I did not summon you here to uphold your oaths to the essences. I summoned you here as friends.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Friends?\u8221\'94 the Destructive said, confused. She stood up and kicked her stool. Instead of clattering onto the stone, it blinked out of existence. \u8220\'93I was not aware that we were friends. I\u8217\'92ve lost count of how many times }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 that one}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  tried to murder me.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 She gestured towards the Creative, whose scowl deepened.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Prophylactic measures,\u8221\'94 the Creative argued. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not the one who broke the first commandment. I am not the one who upset the balance!\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Impartial raised a pacifying hand. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I am not here to arbitrate,\u8221\'94 she said. \u8220\'93I am here to talk.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What could we possibly have to talk about?\u8221\'94 the Destructive asked. \u8220\'93You are both too rooted in this world to understand anything I have to say.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You misunderstand,\u8221\'94 the Impartial said. \u8220\'93I am not here to listen. I am here to talk.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Little good that would do,\u8221\'94 the Creative snipped. \u8220\'93You may talk all you wish, but }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 that one}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  will never listen. Her god separated her mind from sense a long, long time ago.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Both of you...\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Grittted her teeth. A greater display of emotion from her that either the First or the Second had ever seen. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This is the last you\u8217\'92ll ever hear from me, and you will want to hear what I have to say.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Once their attention was gathered, she began her practiced speech.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You two hear different tongues of the Forked God speak. I hear them both. I know what They tell the two of you. I know how They set you against each other. I thought I understood why, but seeing the outcome, I no longer do. And so I must lay down my title as it has long outlived its use, for there is no room for an impartial judge when you both believe that your respective halves of Forked God is the truer God, and that your victory over the other is inevitable. I can only ask, why fight? If your ends are inevitable ends, why lift a finger in defense of your faith? You both claim to worship an almighty power, and yet you }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 kill? }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  If your conflict stayed within the boundaries of survival, there would, but yours is the behavior of fearful creatures. I am tired of it. I haven\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t prayed in century. None were ever answered. You know how They always keep themselves at a distance. I once took this distance to be the measure divinity, but lately, I have begun to wonder.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yours are blasphemous words,\u8221\'94 the Creative said. \u8220\'93Better not let Them hear.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I do not care if they hear, I care only about you. Despite your differences, you share the same basic struggle: you fight day after day, only to have every victory lead into another battle. I know how the word \u8216\'91victory\u8217\'92 has lost all meaning to your ears, for what is a victory if the remnants defeated inevitably find some foothold to nurse their strength, and, in time, start the fight all over again. You have both expressed how you crave a battle to end all battles. That is what I aim to give you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What are you saying?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I am saying that this age will soon be over. Tomorrow, you will be able to kill each other, if you wish. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How will you do that?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well it took a lot of thinking. And dreaming.\u8221\'94 she said fervently. \u8220\'93I had a dream wherein I discovered the words which could contain Them. I assembled a chorus to chant Their names. It sounds silly, but if you heard Their names repeated, each note entering on the finger, each new voice swelling the chord until the wash of noise did shake the earth\u8230\'85such was the echo in the valleys that one and twenty voices blossomed into twelve and thousands!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She was speaking now to the sky, to the stars beyond it. There was a younger face beneath her wrinkling years. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It did subdue Them,\u8221\'94 she claimed. \u8220\'93For an age of peace, it stilled Their being. Then I woke back up into this nightmare\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 into the futility of Their illness. I resolved to be done with it. It was then that I realized that there is only. I\u8217\'92ve chosen to delve into the mysteries of the Black.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 what}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 !?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please. Don\u8217\'92t act like you didn\u8217\'92t already know the answer. You\u8217\'92ve thought of it, too. Only, you\u8217\'92re too much of a . You absolve your conscious by deferring the indignity to me. Which, I hope you know, makes you worse than me. Not only will their death be on your hands, but so will the stain of shirking responsibility. Well, I won\u8217\'92t let you off so easy. When the gods are all dead, you\u8217\'92ll have no one left to repent to but to yourself, and to }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 me}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 . I will not forgive you for it.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I didn\u8217\'92t expect you would.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You know, I\u8217\'92ve come to despise you. More than enemies. At this point, I want more than to defeat you. I want to visit you on your death bed to remind you that we all turn to dust, and that despite all your ambitions you will never live to see them through. Despite how special you think you are, all that's left for you is an eternity of loneliness at best, and an eternity of torture at worst. I want you to know that your entire life\u8217\'92s work was a waste, and the only thing you will experience for the relatively short time you have left is the of my triumph over you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  I say all this to make sure you understand that, after}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  the deed is done, all our conventions will be cast aside. The next time we meet, it will be death.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She flew up into the sky. Such was her speed, that her white robes buzzed behind her. She pushed through the thick of the sky to find the uninterrupted night. The stars, in their sparkling multitude, were always . She floated there in the liminal space between the void and the bright earth.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She drifted up against the chunk of Black. It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s enormity humbled her. She\u8217\'92d seen larger stones, but this was of a substance which defied all size comparison. It would seem larger next to objectively larger things. And though it floated freely, it was, somehow, still embedded in the void; its edges extruded out of the black space which was infinitely distant, all to make a jagged body, chaotically pinched, a spiky complex of scar contractures on the skin of night. An ugly wound from an old and ugly injury. With such a substance, size was not a relational thing, but a deep internal feeling; in size, it felt to her like a small city had been glassed into obsidian, then broken, then smushed up into a ball, then hammered into a shape which evoked despair.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The thing turned, slowly, through its tempted orbit. Its fractaled surface multiplied the points of stars. It turned, slowly, to reveal a flat, cylindrical head that would strike the world like a hammer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 And what was the world, now?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 From this height, she could see it all. She could remember it all.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 That once green paradise was crusted over with history. Grim monuments to abandoned civilizations trimmed every river bend\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 gray lesions on the skin of a dying world. Great pastures which once nursed untold scores of life had been ruined by herds of cattle.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  The waters were all drunk dry. Bare mountains rumpled up the of tectonic plates, old wounds. It had been a slow, slow death. Most of the colors dipped into gray. And there amongst it was her god. Blinding white, and sparkling, H}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 e looked like a fallen star twinkling atop the tallest peak of the Goree mountains. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Of creation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Childhood. The birth of language and its quick evolution. The first kingship. The first sailing ship. The first minted silver coin and the first imitation of it; a thin bit of copper washed in pewter. The urge to horde. The night she gained the sight. Anatomy lessons with the flayed. The long charter of the fleshcraft guild. The temptations of priests. The origins of debt. The operations of war. The shock of famine. King Sixa\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s plan to pot the desert with wells. The explosion of Mount Volgi which poisoned half the continent. The Folzeek revolution and the splintering of the zagoqa tribes. The beginning of table manners. The deep hunger driving demons through the tunnels of the world. Greed chewing at every city\u8217\'92s roots. Salosa\u8217\'92s denuded self becoming a goddess. All these memories were condensed into one big emotion, and the tears were boiled away when the meteor set fire in the atmosphere. When it smashed through the clouds she sank into more primitive categories of feeling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Fear of her father.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Anger at injustice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And finally, guilt.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each wound in her life now seemed like an accident, arbitrary, for how far could her god have seen when He was weaving her fate? He could not see this massive spot of Black coming to end Him.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Black fell upon Him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The collision shook the earth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The soundlessness of space muted her sigh of awe.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 for at A round shockwave spread, swept away the god cloud like it was nothing, flattened the armies battling below it, then went out to the sea to steam the surface of the waters, stir up the magnificent phytoplankton blooms, thousands of miles long, glowing prussian-blue in whirling gyres. The shock went on to circle the globe, sweeping clouds thin, dragging a shade of dust behind it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  into a trancelike state, though through it all, his existential self, her I-me-mine did not completely disappear. In fact, there was enough of her left to sense her own impending doom, the stretching of time, the thinness of her life. Starting with the ever-slowing cosmic tick of the universe, he could extrapolate out, and understood that it would eventually stop ticking completely. At that point, time would freeze completely into a kind of reflective prism, crystallizing around whatever her last twinkling thought might be, and that would be death. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And so the stage was set for the beginning of the end. It was her against the shadow. The gods were dead. One of them would finally win.}}